text.tspan: Performance Improvement of Hybrid Content Based Image Recognition
Devashish Purandare, Amol Rokade, and Prashant Kumar.
Sinhgad College of Engineering, Pune, Savitribai Phule Pune University
Under the guidance of : Prof. Girija G. Chiddarwar

flowRoot.flowPara: Hybrid approach in Content Based Image Retrieval (CBIR) provides higher accuracy as compared to a global approach but at the same time it comes with the high computational complexity of the local approach. Our implementation of the hybrid CBIR system has reduced complexity and better performance than the original approach using various methods such caching, parallelism, map-reduce, approximation and reducing comparisons. Our results indicate that the performance can be improved by a huge margin without sacrificing accuracy.
The following operations are carried out to make the image - scale, rotation and color invariant.
1. Grid shape representation is used to create a binary matrix representing the image.
3. Singular Value Decomposition of child block
4. Divide each distance by the maximum distance to find the %age similarity
8. Using GPU to speed up the system.
9. Map - Filter - Reduce to optimize search
1. Image retrieval with very high accuracy.
2. Database and caching improve the performance several times over the original implementation without affecting accuracy.
3. Multi core processing, and other optimizations improve processing significantly over basic implemntation.
4. Map-filter can improve performance significantly while slightly reducing accuracy.
